-- CGT Union Says Workers at 10 Out of 12 French Refineries Remain on Strike
-- B y   T a r a   P a t e l
-- 2010-10-13T06:14:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/cgt-union-says-workers-at-10-out-of-12-french-refineries-remain-on-strike.html
Workers at ten French refineries out
of 12 remain on strike today as part of a protest against
raising the retirement age, according to the CGT union.  CGT representative Charles Foulard said the situation at
each site varies and some shifts of workers have yet to vote on
the labor action.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tara Patel at 
 tpatel2@bloomberg.net  